I believe it is not a react but regular javascript sytanx error. What you are trying to do in the following is to return some HTML code in a javascript function. 

```
  render() {

     return (
      &lt;View style={styles.container}&gt;   // &lt;View&gt; is a HTML/XML tag/keyword

        &lt;ChatBot steps={steps} /&gt;
      &lt;/View&gt;
    );
  }
```

I believe these tags are not part of java script syntax and you need to return them as a string instead. Some thing like following should work.

```
  render() {

     return (
      `&lt;View style={styles.container}&gt;

        &lt;ChatBot steps={steps} /&gt;
      &lt;/View&gt;`
    );
  }
```

Hope this helps.

